It was an all-white affair as veteran actor and lawyer, Kanayo Kanayo, celebrated his 60th birthday on Sunday at the Muson Centre Onikan, Lagos. Family, friends and associates of the actor turned out in their numbers to felicitate him, with people coming from all walks of life. Appreciating God for sparing his life to witness the day, the actor also thanked his family and friends for the support they have given him over the years. The actor also launched a foundation named, ‘The Kanayo O Kanayo Foundation’ at the event. Highlights of the event included the two ‘triumphant’ entries of the birthday boy, clad in all-white attire. In the second ‘appearance’, Kanayo wore a bowler hat, while the second time, he went for a traditional red cap worn by chiefs in Igboland. He was later joined by his children on stage in to cut the birthday cake in a session anchored by popular comedian, Ayo Makun, aka AY. Notable guests at the event include a presidential aspirant Kingsley Moghalu; a former Chief Executive Officer of Transnational Corporation and Peoples Democratic Party governorship aspirant in the last Anambra State election, Valentine Ozigbo; entrepreneur and socialite, Obinna Oyiegbu, aka Obi Cubana; Big Brother Naija winner, Hazel Onou aka Whitemoney; veteran singer, Zaaki Azzay; actor, Victor Osuagwu; and comedian, Stanley Chibunna, aka Funny Bone. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com